The '''2014 Liège–Bastogne–Liège''' was the 100th running of [[Liège–Bastogne–Liège]], a single-day cycling race. It was held on 27 April 2014 over a distance of {{convert|263|km|1|abbr=off}} and it was the thirteenth race of the [[2014 UCI World Tour]] season. It was won by [[Simon Gerrans]] in a four-rider sprint finish&nbsp;– becoming the first Australian to win the race<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/sport/simon-gerrans-first-aussie-to-win-liegebastogneliege-race/story-fngr0c3f-1226897821607|first=Ron|last=Reed|work=[[Herald Sun]]|publisher=[[The Herald and Weekly Times]]|date=28 April 2014|accessdate=29 April 2014|title=Simon Gerrans first Aussie to win Liege-Bastogne-Liege race}}</ref>&nbsp;– ahead of [[Alejandro Valverde]], [[Michał Kwiatkowski]] and [[Giampaolo Caruso]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingweekly.co.uk/news/latest-news/liege-bastogne-liege-2014-121133|first=Stephen|last=Puddicombe|work=[[Cycling Weekly]]|publisher=[[IPC Media]]|date=27 April 2014|accessdate=29 April 2014|title=Simon Gerrans wins Liege-Bastogne-Liege}}</ref>

==Teams==
As Liège–Bastogne–Liège was a UCI World Tour event, all 18 [[UCI ProTour#List of current UCI ProTeams|UCI ProTeams]] were invited automatically and obligated to send a squad. Seven other squads were given wildcard places, thus completing the 25-team peloton.

The 25 teams that competed in the race were:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/liege-bastogne-liege/start-list|title=Liège–Bastogne–Liège 2014 start list|work=[[Cyclingnews.com]]|publisher=[[Future plc]]|accessdate=27 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427153745/http://www.cyclingnews.com/liege-bastogne-liege/start-list|archive-date=2014-04-27|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>

